Similarly, Walsh said, "we have people who are obese and binge but don't vomit," so they don't fit into the strict definition of bulimia nervosa, which requires both binging and purging.
As each day goes by, full recovery becomes less and less likely for these women, and others like them, experts say.
The disorder is much like bulimia nervosa, but without the purging.
